{"title":"Thousands Separator","link":"https://www.adamkoch.com/2017/06/12/thousands_sep/","pubDate":"Mon, 12 Jun 2017 19:33:15 +0000","dc:creator":"admin","guid":[{"_":"http://www.adamkoch.com/?p=2779","$":{"isPermaLink":"false"}}],"description":[""],"content:encoded":"Thinking outside the box, there are more ways to indicate the thousands separator…\r\n\r\n10<span style=\"color: #808080;\">0</span><span style=\"color: #999999;\">0</span>0<span style=\"color: #808080;\">0</span><span style=\"color: #999999;\">0\r\n</span>1<u>0</u>00<u>0</u>00\r\n10<sup>00</sup>0<sup>00\r\n</sup>10<span style=\"font-size:.9em\">0</span><span style=\"font-size:.8em\">0</span>0<span style=\"font-size:.9em\">0</span><span style=\"font-size:.8em\">0</span>\r\n\r\nNot that it is currently possible to style it as such in an input element.\r\n\r\nUnless you use ‘o’s for the zeros. That could be done:\r\n\r\n10oo0oo\r\n\r\nThose take up less space than adding a comma:\r\n\r\n1,000,000\r\n\r\nIn monospace:\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-family:monospace\">\r\n1,000,000\r\n10<span style=\"color: #808080;\">0</span><span style=\"color: #999999;\">0</span>0<span style=\"color: #808080;\">0</span><span style=\"color: #999999;\">0\r\n</span>1<u>0</u>00<u>0</u>00\r\n10<sup>00</sup>0<sup>00\r\n</sup>10<span style=\"font-size:.9em\">0</span><span style=\"font-size:.8em\">0</span>0<span style=\"font-size:.9em\">0</span><span style=\"font-size:.8em\">0</span></p>","excerpt:encoded":"","wp:post_id":"2779","wp:post_date":"2017-06-12 13:33:15","wp:post_date_gmt":"2017-06-12 19:33:15","wp:post_modified":["2017-06-12 13:33:53"],"wp:post_modified_gmt":["2017-06-12 19:33:53"],"wp:comment_status":["open"],"wp:ping_status":["open"],"wp:post_name":"thousands_sep","wp:status":"publish","wp:post_parent":["0"],"wp:menu_order":["0"],"wp:post_type":"post","wp:post_password":[""],"wp:is_sticky":["0"],"category":[{"_":"Professional","$":{"domain":"category","nicename":"professional"}}],"wp:postmeta":[{"wp:meta_key":["_edit_la